:asteroid rdfs:subClassOf :minor_planet .
text: asteroid is a type of minor planet.

An astronomical object is a type of object that is characterized by having at least one part that is an astronomical body and possessing a quality of geodiversity. It is also defined as an object composed of one or more gravitationally bound structures associated with a position in space, and it is typically surrounded by outer space. Additionally, an astronomical object is related to or synonymously referred to as a celestial object.
A globular star cluster is a type of astronomical object defined as a group of gravitationally bound stars.
A nebula is a type of astronomical object, defined as an interstellar cloud of dust, hydrogen, helium, and other ionized gases.
A galaxy, which is a type of astronomical object, is defined as a gravitationally bound system comprising stars, stellar remnants, interstellar gas, dust, and dark matter.

A dwarf planet is a type of minor planet and is defined as an astronomical body that orbits a star directly. It is massive enough for its own gravity to compress it into a shape maintained by hydrostatic equilibrium, usually a spheroid. However, it shares its orbit with other bodies, such as asteroids or comets.

A minor planet is a type of astronomical body defined as an astronomical object in direct orbit around the Sun that is neither a planet nor exclusively classified as a comet. This category encompasses dwarf planets, asteroids, trojans, centaurs, Kuiper belt objects, and other trans-Neptunian objects.
A planetary atmosphere is a type of atmosphere that surrounds a planet, at least partially, and is defined as an atmosphere which surrounds a planet.

A nitrogen-oxygen planetary atmosphere is a type of planetary atmosphere that is composed primarily of a mixture of dinitrogen and dioxygen gases. This type of atmosphere is defined as a planetary atmosphere which is composed primarily of dinitrogen and dioxygen gas.

Desert pavement is a type of solid surface layer found on the surface of an astronomical body, constituting at least part of some deserts. It is primarily composed of rock, specifically a union of pebble and cobble. Desert pavement is defined as a desert surface covered with closely packed, interlocking angular or rounded rock fragments of pebble and cobble size. It is also exactly synonymous with gibber, reg, saï, and serir.

An astronomical body part is defined as a material part of an astronomical body. It is classified as a type of fiat object part and also as a type of something that is at least part of some astronomical body.

Solid environmental material is equivalent to something that is both an environmental material and possesses at least one characteristic of a solid. It is classified as a type of environmental material and also as a type of entity that has at least one solid quality. Additionally, solid environmental material is defined as an environmental material which is in a solid state.

Liquid environmental material is the same as something that intersects with something that is an environmental material and something that has at least some quality of a liquid. It is a type of fluid environmental material and also a type of something that at least has some quality of a liquid. Moreover, liquid environmental material is defined as an environmental material which is in a liquid state.

The area of deciduous forest is identified as a type of terrestrial environmental zone. It is further categorized as a type that encompasses parts which are a combination of temperate deciduous broadleaf forest, temperate deciduous needleleaf forest, tropical deciduous broadleaf forest, and tropical semi-deciduous broadleaf forest. Additionally, this area is characterized by its adjacency to the atmospheric boundary layer. The deciduous forest is defined as an area on a planet's surface predominantly covered by a forest where the majority of trees lose their foliage at the same time due to seasonal changes. These forests' surfaces, including the canopy, interact directly with an atmospheric column that stretches from the planetary boundary layer to the exosphere with minimal to no physical interruptions. An alternative term for the area of deciduous forest is simply "deciduous forest."

The biosphere is recognized as a compound part of an astronomical body, and it is defined as a section of an astronomical body that encompasses, as parts, all living entities within the gravitational influence of that body, along with the non-living and dead entities with which they interact. Additionally, the biosphere is identified as an entity that, at the very least, includes a collection of organisms as part of its composition.

The hydrosphere is classified as a type of liquid astronomical body part and is specifically identified as something that is at least primarily composed of liquid water. It is defined as an astronomical body part consisting of the combined mass of water located on, under, and over the surface of a planet.

The pedosphere is a type of compound astronomical body part that not only overlaps with the atmosphere, lithosphere, biosphere, and hydrosphere but is also composed primarily of soil. It is defined as an astronomical body part composed of soil, subject to soil formation processes, and found on the surface of a lithosphere.

The photosphere is a type of astronomical body part and is considered a type of entity that constitutes at least a part of some star. It is defined as an astronomical body part composed of those parts of a star, distal from the star's core, from which light is radiated into space.

The planetary photic zone is a type of astronomical body part characterized by being a planetary part which is exposed, at least periodically, to light. It is also related to and synonymously known as the photosphere.

The illuminated biosphere part is categorized as a type of astronomical body part and is also considered a type of entity that constitutes at least a portion of some biosphere. It is defined as an astronomical body part that encompasses those regions of a biosphere that, at least periodically, receive light and where photosynthesis may occur.

An exorheic lake is a type of lake and a type of freshwater body characterized by a unique feature: water constantly flows out of it under almost all climatic circumstances, maintaining low concentrations of dissolved solids relative to endorheic lakes. This type of lake is also precisely known as an open lake.
Eaves is a type of building part, defined as a part of a building roof which overhangs the face of a wall and, normally, projects beyond the side of a building.
Open eaves are a type of eaves defined as overhanging eaves where the rafters and underside of the roof are visible from below.
Closed eaves are a specific type of eaves characterized by their construction where projecting roof members are not visible as they are concealed from view by boarding.
Humid air is a type of air characterized by having some increased humidity and increased levels of water vapor. It is defined as air which has increased levels of water vapor.

Water vapour saturated air is a type of humid air and is defined as air which has a partial pressure of water vapour equal or near equal to its equilibrium vapor pressure at a given temperature. It is exactly synonymous with water-vapour-saturated air and is also relatedly known as wet air.

Water-based rainfall is a type of hydrological precipitation process that involves atmospheric water vapor condensing to form droplets of liquid water, which are massive enough to fall to a planetary surface due to the planet's gravity. This process necessitates the participation of water vapor-saturated air and raindrops. Water-based rainfall is broadly synonymous with "rain fall" and "rainfall," and it is also relatedly referred to as "rain."

A droplet is a type of mass of liquid, defined as a small column of liquid, bounded completely or almost completely by free surfaces which maintains its shape due to the surface tension of the liquid. Additionally, "drop" is a related synonym to droplet.

A raindrop is a type of droplet and is also a type of something that is at least formed as a result of some condensation process. It has the definition: A droplet formed by condensation of vapor in an atmosphere and which is sufficiently massive to overcome atmospheric resistance and fall to a planetary surface due to gravity.

A water droplet is the same as something that is both a droplet and at least composed primarily of some liquid water. It is defined as a droplet of water. Furthermore, a water droplet is a type of droplet and also a type of something that is at least composed primarily of some liquid water.
A water raindrop is a type both of a raindrop and of a water droplet. Furthermore, it is broadly synonymous with raindrop.
A cloud droplet is a type of droplet that is defined as a droplet which is spherical in shape and suspended in an atmosphere, being of too small a mass to be pulled to a planetary surface by gravity.

A water-based cloud droplet is the same as something that intersects with both a cloud droplet and something that is at least composed primarily of liquid water. It is defined as a cloud droplet composed primarily of water and is considered a type of both water droplet and cloud droplet. Moreover, water-based cloud droplet has broad synonyms, including cloud drop and cloud droplet, and an exact synonym, water-based cloud droplet.

Virga is a type of hydrological precipitation process and also a type of process that includes, at least in part, some sublimation processes. It is broadly synonymous with a process in which precipitation falls from a cloud but evaporates or sublimes before making contact with a planetary surface.

Smoke is a type of aerosol and is a type of substance that, at the very least, is composed of parts that are an intersection of gaseous, solid, and liquid environmental materials. Moreover, smoke is formed as a result of some combustion process.

The combustion process is defined as a high-temperature exothermic redox chemical reaction between a fuel and an oxidant, producing oxidized, often gaseous products, in a mixture termed as smoke. It is a type of thermolysis and aerosol formation process. Furthermore, combustion involves materials that are entities with the quality of combustibility and also those that play the role of fuel. In this process, smoke is produced as an output.

Thermolysis is a type of material transformation process that is defined as a chemical decomposition, which involves the separation of a single chemical compound into its two or more elemental parts or to simpler compounds, caused by heat. It is also exactly synonymous with thermal decomposition.

Pyrolysis is a type of thermolysis and also a type of aerosol formation process. It is a process that occurs in the intersection of environmental material and an anaerobic quality. Pyrolysis involves organic material as a participant and has smoke as one of its outputs. Moreover, pyrolysis is defined as a thermolysis process in which organic material is decomposed in the absence of oxygen.

Smog is a type of fog and also a type of environmental material that intersects with something derived from smoke. Additionally, smog plays a role as an environmental contaminant and is primarily composed of an intersection of smoke and fog. Smog is defined as a fog which is intermixed with smoke or other combustion products and their derivatives.

The area of evergreen forest is recognized as a type of vegetated area and alternatively referred to as evergreen forest. This area is classified under a category that encompasses parts of various forests including tropical marine semi-evergreen forest, temperate evergreen needleleaf forest, tropical lowland evergreen broadleaf rain forest, tropical semi-evergreen moist broadleaf forest, and temperate broadleaf evergreen forest. Additionally, the area of evergreen forest is identified as being adjacent to the atmospheric boundary layer. It is defined as an area on a planet's surface predominantly covered by a forest in which the majority of trees retain their foliage throughout the seasons. The surfaces of this area, including the forest canopy, maintain contact with an atmospheric column stretching from the planetary boundary layer to the exosphere with minimal physical interruptions.

Fog is a type of aerosolized liquids and an atmospheric aerosol that consists, at least in part, of a union of water-based cloud droplets and water ice crystals. It is typically located in the atmosphere and is an output of the condensation process, primarily composed of liquid water. Fog is defined as a visible mass of cloud water droplets or ice crystals suspended in the air at or near the surface of an astronomical body and is synonymously related to haar.

Crystal is a type of solid environmental material and something that at least has some structured quality. It is defined as a solid material whose constituents, such as atoms, molecules, or ions, are arranged in a highly ordered microscopic structure, forming a crystal lattice that extends in all directions.

Water ice crystal is a type of crystal and is also a type of something that is at least composed primarily of some water ice. It is defined as a crystal which is primarily composed of water ice. Additionally, water ice crystal has a broad synonym, which is ice crystal.

Hair ice is a type of water ice that forms on dead wood with the assistance of the fungus Exidiopsis effusa and takes the shape of fine, silky hair, a phenomenon that at least occurs in some broadleaf forest biome. It is also known by the exact synonyms "frost beard" and "ice wool."
A flower strip is a type of vegetated area defined as a vegetated area that includes a community of flowering plants providing food for local pollinators.
A flower-rich field margin strip is a type of flower strip that is characterized by being adjacent to agricultural fields. It is defined as a flower strip present at the margins of cultivated fields.

A clathrate material is a type of crystal that is defined as a material primarily composed of a substance arranged as a lattice, which can trap or contain other molecules. This material is also precisely known as a clathrate compound material and a clathrate crystal material.

Methane clathrate is a type of clathrate material defined as a clathrate material in which a large amount of methane is trapped within a crystal structure of water, forming a solid similar to ice. It is exactly synonymous with several terms, including fire ice, gas hydrate, hydromethane, methane hydrate, methane ice, and natural gas hydrate.

The coral bleaching process is a type of ecosystem process and is also a type of process that involves at least some coral reef as a participant. It is defined as an environmental process in which coral expels the symbiotic algae living in its tissue as a result of stress, causing the coral to turn white. Additionally, the coral bleaching process is synonymously related to coral bleaching.

Marl is a type of mineral material that is defined as a mass of calcium carbonate derived from mollusk shells and mixed with silt and clay. It is a type of substance that at least has parts of clay and silt, and is composed primarily of calcium carbonate.
The tropical marine coral reef biome is a type of marine coral reef biome as well as a type of tropical biome. It is defined as a marine coral reef biome located in a region with a tropical climate.

The area of mixed forest is categorized as a type of vegetated area and also as a type of region that at least overlaps or is adjacent to some mixed forest and the atmospheric boundary layer, respectively. It is defined as an area of a planet's surface primarily covered by a forest where the trees are a mixture of those that lose and retain their foliage despite seasonal changes. The surfaces of this area, including the surface of the forest canopy, are in contact with an atmospheric column extending from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere with little to no physical obstruction.
A temperate marginal sea biome is a type of marginal sea biome and also a type of temperate biome. It is defined as a marginal sea biome located in a region with a temperate climate.
The temperate Mediterranean Sea biome, which is a type of Mediterranean Sea biome, is defined as a Mediterranean Sea biome that is subject to temperate climate patterns.

The marine upwelling biome is a type of marine biome, characterized as a type of system that includes, at least in part, elements that are an intersection of environmental systems and factors determined by upwelling. It is defined as a marine biome containing communities adapted to living in an environment influenced by the upwelling process.
The tropical marine upwelling biome is a type of marine upwelling biome and also a type of tropical biome. It is defined as a marine upwelling biome that is subject to tropical climate patterns.

The temperate marine upwelling biome is a specific category of both marine upwelling and temperate biomes. It is defined as a marine upwelling biome situated in areas experiencing temperate climate patterns.

The area of dwarf scrub is categorized as a type of bush area and also as a part of some scrubland area. Additionally, it is recognized as being adjacent to some atmospheric boundary layer. It is defined as an area of a planet's surface which is partly covered by shrubs with ground-hugging stems or low growth habit, in contact with an atmospheric column extending from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere with little to no physical obstruction. The area of dwarf scrub is alternatively termed dwarf scrub and has an exact synonym, area of subshrub.

The turbulent aquatic surface layer is a type of aquatic layer, liquid air water interface layer, surface of an astronomical body, and part of some water body. It is defined as a turbulent surface layer of a water body maintained by strong currents setting over submerged ridges or shoals, or by winds opposing a current. Additionally, it has a broad synonym: overfall.

Overflow structures are a type of human construction with a specific purpose. They are structures built into the container of a water body, designed to allow water to flow out of the container when the volume of the water contained exceeds that of its cavity. Additionally, overflow structures are broadly synonymous with overfalls.

The mouth of a liquid discharge conduit is a specific type of mouth that serves as a site at the terminus of a liquid conveyance conduit where the liquid carried is discharged into the sea or a river. Additionally, it has a broad synonym "overfall."
An electric power system is a type of manufactured product, defined as a network of electrical components used to supply, transfer, and use electric power.

A photovoltaic system is a type of electric power system and also a type of system that includes at least some part of a solar panel array. It is defined as a power system designed to supply usable solar power through photovoltaics, consisting of an arrangement that includes solar panels to absorb and convert sunlight into electricity, a solar inverter to convert the electric current from DC to AC, along with mounting, cabling, and other electrical accessories to establish a functioning system.

A solar panel array is a type of manufactured product defined as a group of solar panels, typically belonging to the same photovoltaic system, arranged to maximize interception of solar radiation. It is also exactly synonymous with the term photovoltaic panel array.

A domestic solar panel array is a specific type of solar panel array that is at least partially integrated into some human dwellings. It is defined as a solar panel array that is incorporated into the power system of a human dwelling. Additionally, the domestic solar panel array is exactly synonymous with the term domestic photovoltaic panel array.

An area of scrub is defined as a part of a planet's surface predominantly covered by shrubs, young trees, or stunted trees. This type of area is categorized within bush areas and is recognized as a part of some scrubland areas. Additionally, it is situated at least adjacent to an atmospheric boundary layer, indicating its surfaces are in direct contact with an atmospheric column that extends from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere, experiencing minimal to no physical obstruction. The term "area of scrub" is alternatively known as "shrub/scrub" and has an exact synonym, "area of shrub."

The ground deformation process is identical to a process that is an intersection of an environmental system process and processes that at least involve some planetary landmass as an input, as well as processes that produce outputs which are an intersection of planetary landmass and have the quality of being deformed. This process is categorized under both environmental system processes and processes that necessarily involve some planetary landmass as an input. Furthermore, the ground deformation process is also classified as a type that results in outputs comprising planetary landmass that possesses the characteristic of being deformed. Additionally, the ground deformation process is defined as a process in which a solid planetary surface undergoes deformation.

A puddle of water is a type of lentic water body. It is defined as a small accumulation of water on a surface, which can form either by pooling in a depression on the surface or by surface tension upon a flat surface.
Ballast water is a type of liquid water and something that is at least contained in some ballast tank. It is defined as water contained in the ballast tanks of sea-going vessels.

A ballast tank is a type of manufactured product that is defined as a compartment within a boat, ship, or other floating structure. This compartment holds water, which is used as ballast to provide stability for a vessel.

Hailfall is a type of hydrological precipitation process and is exactly synonymous with hail fall. It is a type of process that involves at least one participant, which is a hail stone. Furthermore, hailfall is described as a process involving an object aggregate that includes hail stones as members. The definition of hailfall is a hydrological process during which hail stones fall to the surface of an astronomical body.

The precipitation process is a type of material transport process, defined as a process in which a portion of some substance segregates from a material in which that substance or its precursors were dissolved or suspended in and settles due to a force such as gravity or centrifugal force.

A storm is a type of environmental system process, defined as an environmental process in which an environmental system and the processes it participates in are strongly perturbed by external forcings. These forcings typically increase the rates of processes unfolding in the system, relative to their normal rates.

An atmospheric storm is defined as a process in which a portion of an astronomical body's atmosphere is strongly perturbed from its prevailing weather. It falls under the category of storms and is a type of atmospheric process. Furthermore, it is characterized as a phenomenon that includes at least a part that is an intersection of something involving atmospheric wind and something that possesses a quality of an increased rate.

A thunderstorm is a type of convective storm and is also known as an electrical storm or lightning storm. It is characterized by being a type of phenomenon that includes at least some atmospheric lightning. The definition of a thunderstorm is an atmospheric storm that occurs in cumulonimbus clouds and is accompanied by lightning and thunder.

A rainstorm is identified as a type of atmospheric storm, and it is also recognized as a type of occurrence that necessarily includes components that are characterized by water-based rainfall and exhibit qualities of an increased rate. Furthermore, a rainstorm is defined as an atmospheric storm during which intense rainfall occurs.

A hailstorm is a type of icestorm and is also defined as an atmospheric storm during which intense hailfall occurs. Additionally, a hailstorm is a type of phenomenon that includes, at least in part, an event characterized by the intersection of hailfall and an increased rate of some quality.

A snowstorm is a type of atmospheric storm that is also characterized as a type of phenomenon that encompasses at least a part that is an intersection of snowfall and an aspect that possesses an increased rate quality. Moreover, a snowstorm is defined as an atmospheric storm during which intense snowfall occurs.

An icestorm is a type of atmospheric storm characterized by at least having parts such as freezing rainfall and producing outputs like a glaze ice layer. It is defined as an atmospheric storm during which freezing rain falls and accumulates as ice on exposed surfaces. Icestorm is exactly synonymous with glaze event, glaze storm, ice storm, silver storm, and silver thaw. Additionally, it is relatedly synonymous with glaze event and silver thaw.

The area of developed open space is identified as a type of anthropised terrestrial environmental zone and is also classified as a part of or adjacent to dense settlement biomes and the atmospheric boundary layer, respectively. It is defined as an area of a planet's surface, predominantly covered by cultivated or anthropically maintained vegetation, which is planted for recreational, erosion control, or aesthetic purposes, and is interspersed with constructed or manufactured objects and materials. This area directly interacts with an atmospheric column that stretches from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere with minimal to no physical obstructions. Additionally, the area of developed open space is alternatively referred to as developed, open space.

An area of developed space with low usage intensity is a specific type of area of developed space. It is defined as an area of a planet's surface that is mainly covered by cultivated or anthropically maintained vegetation and by constructed or manufactured objects and materials, covering up to approximately half of its extent. These areas are utilized for low-intensity purposes, such as accommodating collections of single-family residential units, and they are in contact with an atmospheric column that extends from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere with little to no physical obstruction. Additionally, an alternative term for an area of developed space with low usage intensity is "developed, low intensity."

An area of developed space with medium usage intensity is a specific category within the broader classification of areas of developed space. It is defined as a region on a planet's surface predominantly covered by constructed or manufactured objects and materials, occupying between half to three-fourths of its area, alongside cultivated or human-maintained vegetation. These areas are designated for medium intensity uses, such as housing dense clusters of single-family residential units. Furthermore, this type of area directly interacts with an atmospheric column that spans from the planetary boundary layer to the exosphere, facing minimal to no physical barriers. Additionally, an alternative term for an area of developed space with medium usage intensity is "developed, medium intensity."

An area of developed space with high usage intensity is a specific type of area of developed space. It is defined as an area of developed space used for high-intensity purposes, such as accommodating dense and multi-occupant residential, commercial, and industrial units. This area comes into contact with an atmospheric column that extends from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere with little to no physical obstruction. Additionally, an alternative term for the area of developed space with high usage intensity is "developed, high intensity."

The area of sedge and forb dominated herbaceous vegetation is recognized as a type of vegetated area and is also categorized under entities adjacent to or interacting with the atmospheric boundary layer. It is defined as an area on a planet's surface primarily occupied by sedges or forbs, which may be interspersed with grasses or grass-like plants. This particular area is in direct contact with an atmospheric column that extends from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere, experiencing minimal to no physical obstructions. Furthermore, an alternative term for the area of sedge and forb dominated herbaceous vegetation is "sedge/herbaceous."

An area of gramanoid or herbaceous vegetation, alternatively termed grassland/herbaceous, is characterized as a type of grassland area. This classification not only denotes a specific grassland area but also categorizes it as a type that is at least adjacent to some atmospheric boundary layer. Furthermore, it is defined as an area of a planet's surface predominantly covered by gramanoid or herbaceous vegetation, which is minimally influenced by intensive human management. This area is in direct contact with an atmospheric column that extends from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere, experiencing little to no physical obstruction.

An area of lichen dominated vegetation is classified as a vegetated area, which is also considered a part of or adjacent to some tundra biome and the atmospheric boundary layer, respectively. It is defined as an area of a planet's surface primarily covered by fruticose or foliose lichens, in contact with an atmospheric column stretching from the planetary boundary layer to the exosphere with minimal physical obstruction. Additionally, it is alternatively referred to as lichens.

An area of moss-dominated vegetation is a type of vegetated area and is also a type of area that is at least adjacent to some atmospheric boundary layer. It is defined as an area of a planet's surface which is primarily covered by mosses and is in contact with an atmospheric column extending from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere with little to no physical obstruction. Additionally, an area of moss-dominated vegetation is alternatively termed as moss.

The area of pastureland or hayfields, also known as pasture/hay, is characterized as a type of area of graminoid or herbaceous vegetation, and it falls under the category of anthropized terrestrial environmental zones. Additionally, it is identified as a type of area that constitutes at least part of some ranches. The definition of an area of pastureland or hayfields is an area of a planet's surface which is partly covered by planted grasses, legumes, or mixtures of grass and legumes. This area is utilized for livestock grazing or the production of seed or hay crops and is in contact with an atmospheric column that extends from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere, with little to no physical obstruction.

The area of cropland is recognized as a type of vegetated area, and it also falls under the category of something that is, at least in part, part of a cropland ecosystem, as well as being adjacent to an atmospheric boundary layer. It is defined as an area of a planet's surface that is partially covered either by annual crops and perennial woody crops or by actively tilled land. This area is in contact with an atmospheric column that extends from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere with little to no physical obstruction. Furthermore, the area of cropland is alternatively termed as cultivated crops.

The area of woody wetland is a type of wetland area, and it is also a type of entity that includes at least a part of some wetland area. Furthermore, it is characterized as a type of region that contains at least part of an area that is a union of forested and scrubland areas. Additionally, an area of woody wetland is a type of area that is adjacent to some atmospheric boundary layer. The area of woody wetland is defined as an area of a planet's surface which is partly covered by forest or shrubland vegetation, where the underlying soil or substrate is periodically saturated with or covered by water. This area is in contact with an atmospheric column that extends from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere with little to no physical obstruction. An alternative term for the area of woody wetland is woody wetlands.

The area of emergent herbaceous wetland is a type of wetland area and also falls under something that is at least part of or adjacent to some wetland ecosystem and the atmospheric boundary layer, respectively. It is defined as an area of a planet's surface primarily covered by perennial herbaceous vegetation, where the underlying soil or substrate is periodically saturated with or covered by water. This area is in contact with an atmospheric column extending from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere with little to no physical obstruction. Additionally, the area of emergent herbaceous wetland is alternatively termed as emergent herbaceous wetlands.

Snowfall is a type of hydrological precipitation process and also a type of process that involves snow as a participant. It is defined as a hydrological process in which irregular aggregates of snow fall to the surface of an astronomical body. Additionally, snowfall has an exact synonym, which is "snow fall".

Freezing rainfall is a type of water-based rainfall which involves several key characteristics. It is defined as water-based rainfall that freezes either upon impact with a surface, forming a coating of clear ice known as glaze, or after percolating through surface layers. This phenomenon occurs under specific conditions, including the presence of a surface layer and a decreased temperature. Additionally, freezing rainfall results from a process that involves water and leads to the production of something frozen. It is broadly synonymous with both "freezing rain" and "freezing rain fall."

The electrostatic discharge process is a type of environmental system process. It is defined as a process during which a sudden flow of electricity occurs, often accompanied by a visible release of photons, between two electrically charged objects due to contact, an electrical short, or dielectric breakdown.

Atmospheric lightning is a type of electrostatic discharge and atmospheric process that involves at least some clouds as participants and produces plasma as an output. It is defined as a sudden electrostatic discharge that occurs during an electrical storm as differentially charged atmospheric entities equalize their charge. Atmospheric lightning is exactly synonymous with lightning.

Intercloud lightning is a type of lightning flash defined as a lightning process during which electrostatic discharge occurs between at least two clouds. It is also precisely known as CC lightning and cloud-cloud lightning.
Intracloud lightning, also known exactly as IC lightning, is a type of lightning flash defined as a lightning process during which electrostatic discharge occurs within a single cloud.

A lightning strike is a type of atmospheric lightning and also a type of event that involves at least one participant, which can either be a planetary surface or an entity that is a material object adjacent to a planetary surface. It is defined as a lightning process during which electrostatic discharge occurs between a cloud and an object on a planetary surface, or the planetary surface itself. Furthermore, a lightning strike is exactly synonymous with both CG lightning and cloud-ground lightning.
A lightning flash is a type of atmospheric lightning, defined as a lightning process during which electrostatic discharge occurs within a single cloud or between multiple clouds.

A blizzard is a type of snowstorm and also a type of phenomenon that involves at least some aeolian transport of snow. It is defined as a severe snowstorm during which snowfall is transported by strong winds and is sustained for several hours. Additionally, blizzard has narrow synonyms including boulbie, buran, and purga.

A ground blizzard is a type of atmospheric storm defined as a storm during which snow that has settled on a planetary surface is resuspended in and transported through its atmosphere by strong winds, sustained for several hours.
A shrimp pond is defined as a lentic water body utilized for the artificial culture of shrimp and is a type of lentic water body that encompasses some crustacean farming process.

The aquaculture process is a planned environmental usage process that occurs in some water body and involves the participation of entities that are either viridiplantae or metazoa. It is defined as a process during which humans rear animals or plants in bodies of water for harvest and consumption. Additionally, the aquaculture process is synonymously related to aquatic farming.

A feasting pit site is a type of archaeological site characterized by its definition as an archaeological location that contains holes humans had dug in the ground, or their remnants. These pits were used for the purpose of storing and distributing food, drink, and both functional or ritualistic implements during communal eating and drinking events.

A geothermally heated river is a type of river defined as a river which is heated by geothermal processes such as heat exchange with lava or hydrothermal percolation. It is also related to the synonym boiling river.

Biocrust, also known as biological crust, is a type of solid surface layer. It is characterized by being part of an ecological community that is capable of photosynthesis. Additionally, biocrust is found in environments that are at the intersection of ecological systems and areas with arid qualities. It is defined as a surface layer of solid environmental material formed through the presence and activity of photosynthetic microbial assemblages colonizing it.

Soil biocrust, also known as biological soil crust, cryptobiotic soil, cryptogamic soil, microbiotic soil, microphytic soil, or soil biological crust, is a specific type of biocrust. It is recognized as a type of surface on an astronomical body and constitutes at least part of some soil surface layers. Soil biocrust is defined as a biocrust formed by photosynthetic microbial assemblages that colonize the surface layer of a portion of arid soil. The successional dynamics of these communities result in a reduction of the soil surface's albedo, imparting stability against erosion, modifying its hydrology, and enhancing its fertility.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:automated_teller_machine rdfs:subClassOf :manufactured_product ;
    :has_definition "An electronic telecommunications device that enables the customers of a financial institution to perform financial transactions, particularly cash withdrawal, without the need for a human cashier, clerk or bank teller." ;
    :has_exact_synonym "automated banking machine",
        "automatic teller machine",
        "automatic telling machine",
        "bankomat",
        "cash machine",
        "cashline",
        "cashpoint",
        "minibank" .
text: An automated teller machine (ATM) is a type of manufactured product defined as an electronic telecommunications device that enables the customers of a financial institution to perform financial transactions, particularly cash withdrawal, without the need for a human cashier, clerk, or bank teller. It is also known by its exact synonyms: automated banking machine, automatic teller machine, automatic telling machine, bankomat, cash machine, cashline, cashpoint, and minibank.

A cloud condensation nucleus, which has the exact synonyms CCN and cloud seed, is defined as a solid or liquid particle, typically 0.2 micrometers in diameter, on which water vapor condenses to seed cloud formation. It is identified as the same as an entity that intersects the mass of environmental material and something that participates, at least to some extent, in the nucleation of cloud condensation. This nucleus is categorized under various types: it is a form of mass of environmental material, an element that is at least partially part of some aerosol, and an entity that actively takes part in the nucleation of cloud condensation. Additionally, it is constituted primarily of materials that are either solid environmental material, liquid environmental material, or a combination of both.

Nucleation of cloud condensation is a type of atmospheric and hydrological process, which involves water vapour and entities that are both material and have qualities of a solid or a liquid. This process is crucial for or directly involved in the cloud formation process. It is defined as a process during which a solid particle or liquid droplet catalyzes the condensation of water vapour in an atmosphere, and is also known as the cloud seeding process.

The ice ablation zone, which is also broadly known as the ablation zone, is a specific type of ice decumulation zone. This zone is characterized by being part of the union of an ice sheet and a glacier. It is defined as an environmental zone that overlaps with a glacier or an ice sheet, where the loss of ice exceeds the gain of ice.

The ice loss process is identified as a type of material decumulation process that specifically involves the decrease in size of an existing ice mass. This process is not only categorized by its input, which is some ice mass, but also by its output, which notably is an entity that is both an ice mass and has the quality of having decreased mass. In terms of its components, the ice loss process encompasses a variety of subprocesses, including melting, sublimation, and ice calving processes, as well as material transport and material transformation processes. The term "ice loss" is used as an exact synonym for the ice loss process, underscoring its role in the reduction of ice mass.

A rubbish landslide is a type of mass wasting defined as a mass wasting process during which refuse from human activities, usually accumulated at a dumping site, falls down a slope under the force of gravity. It is also exactly synonymous with garbage landslide, refuse landslide, and trash landslide.

The ice calving process is a type of mass wasting and is also a type of something that has at least some ice mass as a participant. It is defined as a process during which a part of an ice mass breaks away from the main mass. Additionally, the ice calving process has a broad synonym: calving.

An open animal house falls under the category of animal houses. It is defined as a type of structure that is at least partially encompassed by a building envelope and possesses a quality of openness. Specifically, an open animal house is characterized as an animal house that is only partially surrounded by a building envelope.

The glacial ice ablation process is a type of englacial process, glacial ice loss, and something that at least occurs in some ice ablation zone. It is defined as an ice loss process which occurs in the low-altitude area of a glacier or ice sheet below the firn layer.

The water ice sublimation process is defined as a sublimation process during which water ice transitions into a gaseous state. This process is identical to an intersection of processes that are characterized by sublimation, processes that require at least some water ice as an input, and processes that produce at least some water vapour as an output. It is categorized as a type of sublimation process, a type of hydrological process, a type of process that requires at least some water ice as input, and a type of process that results in the production of at least some water vapour as output.

A closed animal house is a type of animal house and is also a type of entity that encompasses at least a part that is an intersection of a building envelope and an entity that possesses a quality of being closed. Furthermore, a closed animal house is defined as an animal house that has a complete building envelope.
An animal cage, which is a type of manufactured cage, is defined as a manufactured cage that may be used to confine, contain, or protect an animal. Additionally, it has a broad synonym: cage.

A petting zoo is a type of zoological garden, which is defined as a zoological garden containing domesticated non-human animals and some wild non-human animals that are docile enough for humans to touch and feed. Additionally, a petting zoo has an exact synonym "petting farm" and is also related to the term "children's zoo."

A plumbing drain, also known as a drain or drainage channel, is a type of artificial channel. It is defined as an artificial channel that transports unwanted water or waste liquids away from their source, either to a more useful area, a receptacle, or into sewers or stormwater mains as waste discharge to be released or processed.

An abattoir, also known exactly as a slaughter plant or slaughterhouse, is a type of industrial building. It is defined as a facility in which non-human animals are slaughtered and processed for human consumption. Additionally, abattoir is relatedly synonymous with butchery and meat processing building.

A knackery is a type of industrial building defined as a facility where non-human animals are slaughtered and processed, but not for human consumption. It is exactly synonymous with the term knacker's yard.

A day care building is a type of commercial building, which is defined as a building used to care for a human child during the working day by a person outside the child's immediate family, other than that child's legal guardians. Furthermore, a day care building has exact synonyms, including "child care building" and "daycare building."

A fish processing building is a type of food processing building defined as a building in which fish are subject to a series of operations to prepare them for human consumption. Additionally, it has a related synonym, "fish factory."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:mushroom_environment rdfs:subClassOf :anatomical_entity_environment .
text: mushroom environment is a type of anatomical entity environment.

An ecological corridor is a type of ecosystem defined as an ecosystem that bridges two or more adjoining ecosystems, facilitating the movement or propagation of organisms between them. It is also related to several synonyms including animal corridor, green corridor, habitat corridor, and wildlife corridor.

A migration path is a type of ecological corridor and is defined as an ecological corridor through which organisms move during a migration process. It is exactly synonymous with migration corridor and is also relatedly synonymous with migratory route.

A nursing home is a type of healthcare facility defined as a building in which nursing aides and skilled nurses provide care and treatment to residents who have significant difficulty coping with the required activities of daily living. It has broad synonyms such as intermediate care facility, long-term care facility, old people's home, and skilled nursing facility. Additionally, nursing home is exactly synonymous with care home, convalescent home, and rest home.
A residential building is a type of human house, defined as a human house that serves as a long-term shelter for its inhabitants and within which they store personal property.

A restaurant is a type of commercial building that is defined as a building within which food and drink are prepared and served to customers in exchange for money or other goods and/or services. It also has an exact synonym, eatery.

A campground is a type of anthropogenic geographic feature, defined as a part of an ecosystem which may be or has been used for one or more overnight stays by humans sheltering in tents, camper vans, caravans, or improvised shelters. It is precisely synonymous with terms such as camping ground, camping pitch, camping site, and campsite.

A dedicated campground is a type of campground that is defined as a campground which has been modified by humans to provide and maintain facilities for camping, including fire pits, road access, latrines, and garbage bins.

An impromptu campground is a type of campground that is defined as a campground which has no pre-existing facilities installed or maintained by humans, usually found outside of anthropised ecosystems.

A hot tub is a type of manufactured product defined as a manufactured product which may hold a volume of heated water suitable for one or more humans to bathe in, usually for the purposes of hydrotherapy or pleasure. It is broadly synonymous with a spa and has a narrow synonym, Jacuzzi.

A time crystal is a type of environmental material that is defined as an open system in non-equilibrium with its environment, exhibiting time translation symmetry breaking. It is also exactly synonymous with a space-time crystal.

Fissure water is a type of liquid water and is also known as fracture water. It is defined as water which is partially contained within a fissure or a geological fracture, meaning it is at least partially surrounded by some geological fracture.

A planetary subsurface zone is a type of subsurface zone found within an astronomical body, which at least overlaps some planetary structural layer and is adjacent to some planetary surface. It is defined as regions of a planet that are not exposed to the planet's atmosphere or space, often comprising parts of one or more planetary structural layers.

A continental subsurface zone is a type of planetary subsurface zone, which is also defined as a type of entity that at least overlaps some continental crust and is adjacent to some planetary landmass. Moreover, it is defined as a region which overlaps parts of one or more planetary structural layers located below a continental landmass.
A vegetated hill is a type of hill defined as a hill which has a surface that is partially or wholly covered by plant communities.
A microplastic particle is a type of piece of plastic and is defined as a piece of plastic with a diameter of less than five millimetres. It is also related to the synonym "microplastic."

A primary microplastic particle is a type of microplastic particle that is defined as a microplastic particle which is the direct output of a manufacturing process. It has exact synonyms such as Primäres Mikroplastik, microplastica primaria, and microplástico primario. Additionally, it is relatedly synonymized with microplastic.

A secondary microplastic particle is a type of microplastic particle that is derived from the breakdown of larger plastic debris. It is exactly synonymous with "Sekundäres Mikroplastik," "microplastica secondaria," and "microplástico secundario." Additionally, it has a related synonym, "microplastic."

Ecotone is a type of ecosystem and also a type of something that at least overlaps some biome, as well as a type of something that has at least 2 biome components. Additionally, ecotone has the definition of being an environmental system which bridges two or more biomes and includes ecological communities that blend these biomes' phylogenetic and phenotypic compositions.

The polar tree line ecotone is a specific type of tree line ecotone that serves as a bridge between a subpolar coniferous forest biome and a tundra biome. This ecotone is characterized by an overlapping area that intersects both the tundra biome and the subpolar coniferous forest biome. It is defined as an ecotone which bridges these two biomes. Additionally, the polar tree line ecotone is also known by its related synonym, the Arctic tree-line ecotone.
Lichen woodland is a type of conifer woodland characterized by an understory that is partially covered by lichen mats and tundra-like vegetation.

The water ice formation process is a type of material congelation process and is also considered a hydrological process. It is characterized by being a process that necessarily involves the freezing and desublimation of water vapor into ice. Additionally, this process requires inputs that are a combination of liquid water and substances that possess qualities of both a gas and a liquid. The output of this process is water ice. Furthermore, the water ice formation process is defined as a material transformation process during which water ice is formed.

The natural environment is equivalent to an intersection of the environmental system and the complement of anything that is at least formed as a result of some level of anthropisation. It is a subtype of the environmental system and is defined as an environmental system in which minimal to no anthropisation has occurred, with non-human agents being the primary determinants of the system's dynamics and composition. Additionally, the natural environment is alternatively termed as a non-anthropised environment or a non-anthropized environment.

Anthropisation, which is the same as something that intersects the anthropogenic ecosystem conversion process and something that at least has input from some natural environment, and something that at least has output of some anthropogenic environment, is a type of anthropogenic ecosystem conversion process. It is also categorized as a type that involves at least some input from a natural environment and is recognized as a type that results in at least some output of an anthropogenic environment. Moreover, anthropisation is defined as a process during which a natural environmental system is altered by human action and has the exact synonym "anthropization."

A tree line ecotone is a type of ecotone defined as an ecotone which overlaps at least one biome that supports the growth and persistence of trees and at least one that does not. As conditions become less favorable along this ecotone, tree growth becomes sparse and trees appear stunted before ceasing altogether. It is exactly synonymous with tree line, tree-line, and treeline.

The alpine tree line ecotone is a specific type of tree line ecotone that is part of some elevated landform. It is defined as a tree line ecotone across which trees cease to grow due to the low temperatures or duration of snow cover that occur at increased elevations above mean sea level. Additionally, the alpine tree line ecotone has exact synonyms including alpine tree line, alpine tree-line, and alpine treeline.

The desert tree line ecotone is a specific type of tree line ecotone and also falls under the category of entities overlapping some desert biome. It is defined as a tree line ecotone across which trees cease to grow due to insufficient water availability because of a lack of water-based precipitation. Furthermore, it is exactly synonymous with terms such as desert tree line, desert tree-line, and desert treeline.

The desert alpine tree line ecotone, which also goes by the exact synonyms desert-alpine tree line, desert-alpine tree-line, and desert-alpine treeline, is a specific type of desert tree line ecotone. It is also a type that at least partially overlaps some alpine tree line ecotones. The desert alpine tree line ecotone is defined as a tree line ecotone where trees cease to grow due to insufficient water availability. This lack of water is caused by exposure to increased solar radiation and a lack of rainfall.

A double tree line ecotone is a specific type of tree line ecotone characterized by a tree line ecotone that includes gaps in tree coverage due to reduced biodiversity in tree-forming plant species. These gaps occur above the alpine tree line for some species yet below the desert tree line for others, with no species having intermediate tolerances present. This concept is also precisely referred to as double tree line, double tree-line, and double treeline.

A terrestrial planet, also known as a rocky planet or telluric planet, is a type of planet that is composed primarily of silicate rocks or metals, as per its definition. This category of planets is characterized by being the intersection of planets and entities that are at least composed primarily of a combination (union) of rock and metallic material. Furthermore, terrestrial planets are relatedly referred to as Earth-like planets, emphasizing their similarity to Earth in terms of composition.
A primary atmosphere is a type of planetary atmosphere that is formed as a result of the accretion of gaseous matter from the accretion disc of the planet's star.
A secondary atmosphere is a type of planetary atmosphere defined as one which has formed as a result of its planet's volcanic activity, or by the accumulation of material from comet impacts.
A tertiary atmosphere is a type of planetary atmosphere defined as one that has formed as a result of biotic processes modifying a secondary atmosphere.

Diatomite is a type of sedimentary rock, known by the exact synonyms kieselguhr and kieselgur, and has related synonyms D.E. and diatomaceous earth. It is defined as a sedimentary rock primarily composed of fossilized, siliceous remains of diatoms mixed with varying amounts of other clays and minerals. Diatomite is composed of several substances; it at least has parts of aluminium oxide, iron oxide, and diatomaceous earth. Furthermore, it comprises something that is an intersection of silicon dioxide and something that at least derives from bacillariophyta.

A diatomite particle is a type of piece of rock and something that is at least primarily composed of diatomite. It is defined as a piece of rock which is primarily composed of diatomite: the fossilized, siliceous remains of diatoms mixed with varying amounts of other clays and minerals. The exact synonyms for a diatomite particle include kieselguhr particle, kieselgur particle, particle of diatomaceous earth, particle of diatomite, piece of diatomaceous earth, and piece of diatomite. Additionally, it has related synonyms such as D.E. and diatomaceous earth.
Industrial wastewater is a type of wastewater that is produced by industrial activity and is characterized by containing chemical contaminants other than those associated with urine and fecal matter.

A constructed swimming pool is a type of human construction defined as a construction designed to hold water in which humans may swim or perform other leisure activities. It is broadly synonymous with the term "pool" and has exact synonyms including "paddling pool," "swimming bath," "swimming pool," and "wading pool."

A private swimming pool is a type of constructed swimming pool defined as a constructed swimming pool owned by a non-governmental legal entity or a collective of such entities. It also has broad synonyms such as "pool" and "swimming pool."
A public swimming pool is a type of constructed swimming pool that is owned by a governmental or state entity. It is broadly synonymous with both "pool" and "swimming pool."

Water intake is a type of human construction and also a type of structure that is at least adjacent to something which is a union of something that forms a channel of a watercourse and a channel. Furthermore, water intake is defined as a hydraulic-engineering installation that transports water in specified amounts, of a specified quality, and in accordance with a water-consumption plan, from a source of supply into a conduit.

A cafeteria is a type of restaurant and it is defined as a building which provides the site for food services with little or no waiting staff furnishing table service. Additionally, cafeteria has a related synonym, canteen.

Delicatessen, also known exactly as deli, is a type of grocery store. It is defined as a food shop which sells a selection of food products that are not typical dietary components of the human population it is co-located with.
A food truck is a type of truck that is equipped to cook and sell food.

A hypoxic lake is defined as a lake which is primarily composed of hypoxic water, essentially being the same as something that intersects a lake and something that is at least composed primarily of hypoxic water. An oxic lake is a type of lake that is the same as something that intersects a lake and something that is at least composed primarily of some oxic water. A lake with an oxic hypolimnion is equivalent to a lake that intersects with a feature having at least a part that is an intersection of hypolimnion with a component primarily composed of oxic water. Weather is a type of environmental variability and is defined as environmental variability which inheres in an astronomical body part or in outer space.
Atmospheric weather is a type of weather and is also a type of something that at least has the characteristic of some atmosphere. It is defined as weather which inheres in an atmosphere.

Environmental variability is a type of environmental condition defined as a condition which inheres in an environmental system due to that system undergoing variation in its composition, the distribution of the qualities its components bear, and/or in the processes which occur within it and in which it participates.
Climate is a type of environmental disposition, defined as the disposition of an environmental system, particularly those influencing atmospheres, to manifest a cyclic pattern of weather over time.

The cloud formation process is a multifaceted atmospheric, hydrological, and material accumulation process characterized by the involvement of water vapor as a participant and the production of clouds as an output. It is inherently connected to, or causally influenced by, the nucleation of cloud condensation. Defined as a process during which water vapor condensing in the atmosphere aggregates into clouds, the cloud formation process is precisely synonymous with cloud formation.

The particulate matter formation process is a type of material transformation process that involves the creation of microscopic solid or liquid objects. This process is characterized by producing particulate environmental material as at least one of its outputs. Moreover, it is also referred to by the synonym "particle formation."

Atmospheric aerosol formation is identical to an intersection of an aerosol formation process and a process that occurs in some atmosphere. This formation is a specific type of both aerosol formation process and atmospheric process. It is defined as an aerosol formation process which occurs in an atmosphere. Moreover, atmospheric aerosol formation is exactly synonymous with itself.

The formation of a solid aerosol in an atmosphere is equivalent to the intersection of atmospheric aerosol formation and processes that at least output some aerosolized solids. It is both a type of atmospheric aerosol formation and a type of process that outputs aerosolized solids. This process is defined as a phenomenon during which an aerosol, consisting of solid particulates suspended in a gas, is formed in an atmosphere. Additionally, "formation of solid particles in an atmosphere" serves as a related synonym to the formation of a solid aerosol in an atmosphere.

The formation of a liquid aerosol in an atmosphere is equivalent to something that is at the intersection of atmospheric aerosol formation and something that at least outputs some aerosolized liquids. This process is a specific type of atmospheric aerosol formation and also falls under the category of processes that at least result in the production of aerosolized liquids. The definition of the formation of a liquid aerosol in an atmosphere is the process during which an aerosol, which consists of droplets of liquid suspended in gas, is formed within an atmosphere. Additionally, this process is synonymously related to the formation of liquid droplets and the formation of liquid particles in an atmosphere.

Aerosolised liquids are the same as aerosols that are primarily composed of materials from the environment that have the quality of a liquid. They are a type of aerosol and also a kind of substance that has either the quality of a solid or a liquid. Additionally, aerosolised liquids are surrounded by air and primarily composed of environmental materials that possess liquid qualities. The definition of aerosolised liquids is an aerosol whose non-gaseous parts are primarily made up of liquid droplets. Furthermore, "liquid aerosol" is an exact synonym for aerosolised liquids.

Aerosolised solids are equivalent to substances that intersect between aerosols and substances that are primarily composed of materials that are both environmental and solid in quality. They are categorized as a type of aerosol and also fit the classification of substances that have qualities of either a solid or a liquid. Additionally, these solids are characterized by being primarily surrounded by air and composed of environmental materials that have solid qualities. Aerosolised solids are defined as aerosols whose non-gaseous parts are mainly made up of solid particles and are exactly synonymous with solid aerosol.

The formation of a solid aerosol from gaseous material in an atmosphere is equivalent to the intersection of processes that involve the formation of a solid aerosol in an atmosphere and processes that necessarily involve inputting some gaseous environmental material, as well as processes that necessarily result in the output of aerosolized solids. This formation is categorized as a type of formation of a solid aerosol in an atmosphere and also as a type of process that requires the input of some gaseous environmental material. It is defined as a process during which microscopic solid particulates are formed from gaseous materials in an atmosphere. This process is broadly synonymous with the atmospheric formation of a solid aerosol, the formation of a solid aerosol in an atmosphere, and the formation of a solid aerosol in the atmosphere. Additionally, it is relatedly synonymous with the formation of solid particles from gaseous material in an atmosphere.

The formation of a liquid aerosol from gaseous material in an atmosphere is equivalent to an intersection involving the processes of the formation of a liquid aerosol in an atmosphere, and those that necessitate at least some gaseous environmental material as input and result in the production of aerosolized liquids. This process is classified as a type of both the formation of a liquid aerosol in an atmosphere and activities that require the input of some gaseous environmental material. It is defined as a process during which microscopic liquid droplets are formed from gaseous materials in an atmosphere. Additionally, the formation of a liquid aerosol from gaseous material in an atmosphere is precisely synonymous with the atmospheric formation of a liquid aerosol, the formation of a liquid aerosol in an atmosphere, and the formation of a liquid aerosol in the atmosphere.
